NLquery: Q1: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
prompt: Translate the NL query to SQL using the ModelServices(bmid,sid,version) table.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: WITH counts AS (SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS usage_count FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version), maxes AS (SELECT sid, MAX(usage_count) AS max_usage FROM counts GROUP BY sid) SELECT c.sid, c.version, c.usage_count FROM counts c JOIN maxes m ON c.sid = m.sid AND c.usage_count = m.max_usage ORDER BY c.sid;

NLquery: Q1: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS usage_count FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid;

NLquery: Q1: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
prompt: Prompt asking for most frequent version but missing grouping details.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM ModelServices WHERE version IN (SELECT MAX(version) FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid);

NLquery: Q2: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt: Translate NL query using User, AgentCreator, BaseModel and ModelServices tables.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ms.sid FROM ModelServices ms JOIN BaseModel b ON ms.bmid = b.bmid JOIN AgentCreator ac ON b.creator_uid = ac.uid JOIN User u ON ac.uid = u.uid WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh' GROUP BY ms.sid HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ms.bmid) = (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM BaseModel b2 JOIN AgentCreator ac2 ON b2.creator_uid = ac2.uid JOIN User u2 ON ac2.uid = u2.uid WHERE u2.username = 'user_iuwrh');

Q2: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.

NLquery: Q3: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt: Translate NL query using CustomizedModel and ModelConfigurations.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT DISTINCT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel cm WHERE cm.mid NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT mc.mid FROM ModelConfigurations mc) ORDER BY cm.mid;
